President Trump delivered a speech in the Rose Garden, highlighting the benefits of the tax cuts and reforms that his administration has implemented. He thanked members of Congress who helped pass the tax cuts and recognized Vice President Pence and members of his Cabinet. The President emphasized that the tax cuts are putting more money in the pockets of hardworking Americans and creating jobs. He also spoke about the positive impact of the tax cuts on various industries, including trucking, manufacturing, and small businesses. The President mentioned that the tax cuts have led to wage growth, record low unemployment rates for Hispanics and African-Americans, and increased investment in American manufacturing. He also discussed ongoing negotiations with China, Canada, and Mexico on trade deals and the administration's efforts to reduce regulations. The President concluded by expressing his belief in the American spirit and the restoration of American prosperity.